To address your concerns:

That's fine if you figured out the twist too early and it's also fine that you didn't enjoy the article as a result. I try to write my stuff to be accessible to a general audience, and sometimes that means not getting super weird and esoteric with my reveals.
They logged it as an SCP post-hoc because it disappeared. One can safely assume that it wasn't an SCP and wasn't connected to the other two 5153 files until this happened.
To be fair, this was put together quite hastily, as it was a jamcon entry. Additionally, my preferred style in general doesn't tend to waste any time. I viewed this as a simple set up, build up, and reveal, and played it as such. That didn't work for you, but that's fine.


Thanks for the read and the thoughtful comment, even if you didn't enjoy :D







